# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the user is
#   responsible for mapping their own environment. But for an application, it can be
#   helpful to include them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, they may get conflicts,
#   and they can choose to ignore Pipfile.lock.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is location-specific and should be committed, but
#   sometimes it might be ignored if there are cross-platform issues.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is location-specific and should be committed, but
#   sometimes it might be ignored if there are cross-platform issues.
# pdm.lock

